column1: A has-a relationship is the best description for:

A Person has first name. last name and relative's. A Relative can be Sister. Brother. Spouse or Child. A Relative is also a Person. it means that a relative also has relative's. There are six classes in this UML class diagram. What class diagram is best ?
column3: Person is an abstract class; Relative class inherits from Person; Sister. Brother. Spouse. Child class inherits from Relative class. Person has reflexive association (0..*).
column4: Person is an abstract class; Relative class inherits from Person; Sister. Brother. Spouse. Child class inherits from Relative class. Person class has an unidirectional aggregation with Relative class (0..*).
column5: Person is a normal class; Relative is an abstract class; Sister. Brother. Spouse. Child class inherits from Relative class. Person class has an aggregation with Relative class (0..*). and Relative class has an association with Person class (1)
column6: Person is a normal class; Relative is an interface; Sister. Brother. Spouse. Child class implements from Relative class. Person class associates with Relative class (0..*)

Given an immutable class A with two attributes X and Y. X is an immutable object (for example String. Integer. Long.) and Y is a mutable object (for example Date). Which source code is incorrect ?
column3: public final class A { private final String X; private final Date Y; A (String x. Date y) { this.X = x; this.Y = y;} String getX(){ return this.X; } void setX(String x){this.X = x;} Date getY(){ return Y} void setY(Date y) {this.Y = y;}}
column4: public final class A { private final String X; private final Date Y; A (String x. Date y) { this.X = x; this.Y = y;} String getX(){ return this.X; } Date getY(){ return Y;}}
column5: public final class A { private final String X; private final Date Y; A (String x. Date y) { this.X = x; this.Y = new Date(y.getTime());} String getX(){ return this.X; } Date getY(){ return new Date(Y.getTime());}}
